The author of the article describes their favorite place to take in America's history in Washington, D.C. - the Vice President's Ceremonial Office in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building. The room is filled with historical items and is used for various purposes such as swearing in ceremonies, roundtables, and meetings. The office has ties to the Navy, with reminders of its naval origins throughout. The Theodore Roosevelt Desk is also present, which has been signed by several Presidents and Vice Presidents. The author reflects on the significance of the office and their role as an intern in serving their country.